title: PM wants quick passage of China trade deal
text:
Tue, Sep 8, 2015, 7:23 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 hrs 37 mins PM wants quick passage of China trade deal AAP – 6 minutes ago Print 
Tony Abbott will call on parliament to fully support the trade deal his government has sealed with China. 
The prime minister will move a motion on Tuesday afternoon asking the House of Representatives to note the enormous economic potential from the agreement and acknowledge that it must be passed by year's end for Australian business to benefit. 
Labor has concerns about parts of the agreement it says would let Chinese businesses bring in cheaper workers at the expense of Australian jobs. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Finance News Update, what you need to know AAP
